#create regression model
#import packages
import pandas as pd
import statsmodels.api as sm

# specify the dependent variable and independent variables
y = data['SEP']
X = data[['TAY', 'TAY%', 'REC', 'TAR', 'CTCH%', 'YDS', 'TD', 'YAC/R', 'xYAC/R', '+/-']]

# add a constant term to the independent variables
X = sm.add_constant(X)

# create the multiple regression model
model = sm.OLS(y, X)

# fit the model to the data
results = model.fit()

# print the summary of the regression analysis
print(results.summary())

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
# define the independent and dependent variables
x_var = 'SEP'
y_vars = ['TAY', 'TAY%', 'REC', 'TAR', 'CTCH%', 'YDS', 'TD', 'YAC/R', 'xYAC/R', '+/-']

# create subplots for each dependent variable
fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=5, figsize=(20, 10))
axes = axes.ravel()

# loop through each dependent variable and create a scatter plot
for i, y_var in enumerate(y_vars):
    axes[i].scatter(df[x_var], df[y_var], alpha=0.5)
    axes[i].set_xlabel(x_var)
    axes[i].set_ylabel(y_var)
    axes[i].set_title(y_var)

# adjust spacing between subplots and display the plot
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

WHY USE ALL: I am proceeding with the 68 players who met all requirements met because I am looking for Separation's relation to success. Therefore, I want to look at the recievers who have excelled more than most in every category. For this method, we consider that "success" in the NFL includes being above average in all four of our significantly related statistics: Separation, Catch Percentage, Receiving Yards, and Targets. aspect that is valuable to my analysis. we can assume that these players are successful.

To remind, my Model says that recievers with more Separation get less yards on average, but get thrown to more often and have a higher probability of catching the ball. My results from removing the player duplicates state that over a third of the "successfull" players in this dataset prove that my Model's assumptions are indeed true.

        prev_year = row

df_select = successful_wrs[['PLAYER NAME', 'YEAR', 'SEP', 'CTCH%', 'YDS', 'TAR']]

# create a new column 'Increase' which indicates if the player increased in all three categories and decreased in yards
df_grouped['Increase'] = ((df_grouped['SEP'].diff() > 0) & (df_grouped['CTCH%'].diff() > 0) & (df_grouped['TAR'].diff() > 0) & (df_grouped['YDS'].diff() < 0)).astype(int)

# get the players who meet the criteria
increased = df_grouped[df_grouped['Increase'] == 1]

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# Create a dataframe to store the data
data = pd.DataFrame({
    'Year': [2020.0, 2020.0, 2021.0, 2022.0],
    'Player Name': ['Cole Beasley', 'Tyler Lockett', 'Tyreek Hill', 'Tyler Lockett'],
    'Increase': [1, 1, 1, 1]
})

# Group the data by year and player name
grouped_data = data.groupby(['Year', 'Player Name']).sum()['Increase']

# Create a bar plot to represent the results
grouped_data.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(8,6))
plt.title('Number of Players with Increase in Performance by Year')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Number of Players')
plt.show()
